                     <interp inst="def1-2145-18470920" type="given" value="MARTHA"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">MARTHA FIELD</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18470920-2145-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470920-2145-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18470920-2145-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing 27 yards of printed cotton, value 11<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18470920-name-618" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-618" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-618" type="surname" value="BROWN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-618" type="given" value="JOHN HACKMAN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18470920-2145-offence-1 t18470920-name-618"></join>John Hackman Brown</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184709200085"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470920-name-619" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-619" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-619" type="surname" value="WILLIAMSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-619" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN WILLIAMSON.</persName>
                  </hi> I am in the service of Mr. John Hackman Brown, a linen draper, in High-street, Aldgate. On the 25th of Aug., about half-past eleven o'clock, I was in the cellar, and saw the prisoner and two other women come over the grating—they pulled a piece of cotton about which was on a chair, and the prisoner drew it under her shawl—I ran up and took her—she dropped the cotton—this now produced is it—I gave the prisoner to a police-man—I had not lost sight of her.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE.</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you not lose sight of her while you were coming up out of the cellar? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes, I did then—this printed cotton was on a chair over the grating—the chair did not cover the whole grating—when I came up, the prisoner was about, a dozen doors off—she dropped the cotton about the same place—I stooped and picked it up, and threw it into the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470920-name-620" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-620" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-620" type="surname" value="DREW"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-620" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM DREW.</persName>
                  </hi> I am draper in Old Change—I was passing, and saw the prisoner drop the print.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q</hi> You did not know the print? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No.—the witness put his hand on the prisoner's shoulder—she dropped it, and he took it up.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18470920-name-621" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-621" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-621" type="surname" value="NORDON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18470920-name-621" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GRORGE NORDON.</persName>
                  </hi> I am a tobacconist—I saw the prisoner take the print, and put it partly under her shawl.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Did she take it up and put it down, and then take it up again? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes; and then the witness took her.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18470920-2145-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18470920-2145-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
